Package org.logevents.impl

Class LoggerDelegator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.logevents.impl.LoggerDelegator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LoggerConfiguration, Logger, LocationAwareLogger
    public abstract class LoggerDelegator
extends Object
implements LoggerConfiguration
    Internal implementation of SLF4J Logger. Uses levelThreshold, ownObserver and inheritParentObserver as configuration state and calculates observer and effectiveThreshold based on these. Uses LogEventGenerator internal class as strategy pattern to either ignore everything at a given level or create a LogEvent.
    Author:
    Johannes Brodwall

      • levelThreshold

        protected Level levelThreshold
        Configuration value. Set from LogEventFactory

      • ownObserver

        protected LogEventObserver ownObserver
        Configuration value. Set from LogEventFactory

      • inheritParentObserver

        protected boolean inheritParentObserver
        Configuration value. Set from LogEventFactory

      • observer

        protected LogEventObserver observer
        Calculated value. If inheritParentObserver is true, combines ownObserver with parent observer, otherwise set to ownObserver.

      • effectiveThreshold

        protected Level effectiveThreshold
        Calculated value. If levelThreshold is set, uses this otherwise uses parent's effectiveThreshold.
